creator: William Cowper
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 5 recordings of Report On an Adjudged Case by William Cowper. This was the Weekly Poetry project for December 29, 2013. William Cowper was an English poet and hymnodist. One of the most popular poets of his time, Cowper changed the direction of 18th century nature poetry by writing of everyday life and scenes of the English countryside. (summary from Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (6MB)
